Date: Thu, 27 Feb 2025 18:39:58 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 201/206] registries: generate registries_selector.hpp

Enhance parse_registries.py to generate the registries_selector.hpp
so that it does not need to be generated by hand.

Note that as part of this, additional registries are now emitted for
Redfish.  These registries were already being generated but they were
missing the header hook that allowed them to be exposed.

Tested:
```
$ curl -s -k https://localhost:18080/redfish/v1/Registries/ | jq '.Members | map(."@odata.id")'
[
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/Base",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/Composition",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/Environmental",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/EthernetFabric",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/Fabric",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/HeartbeatEvent",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/JobEvent",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/License",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/LogService",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/NetworkDevice",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/OpenBMC",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/Platform",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/Power",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/ResourceEvent",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/SensorEvent",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/StorageDevice",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/TaskEvent",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/Telemetry",
  "/redfish/v1/Registries/Update"
]
```

Signed-off-by: Patrick Williams <patrick@stwcx.xyz>
